  "style": "IEEE",
  "texts": [
    "In particular, the UV convergence at χ → ∞ is guaranteed by the time-ordering and the Bunch-Davies initial condition, as mentioned above.",
    "On the other hand, the IR convergence at χ → 0 is not automatic and is generally model-dependent.",
    "For instance, a λσ 4 self-interaction for a massless σ field can bring a logarithmic divergence ln(-η) in the IR limit, which after Wick rotation (4.5) brings an imaginary factor of ln e -i(π/2) = -iπ/2.",
    "An odd number of such λσ 4 insertions would lead to a complex ψ n in general.",
    "One can also view this as a consequence of scale invariance spontaneously broken by the IR cutoff [38]."
  ],
